items.description:
Sermon 1 of the 4 part series, Family Matters

The future of America rests on the shoulders of the father. As the authority figure in your home, will you read the Word of God, pray with your children and lead them in the way of the Lord? Or will you let the schoolhouse and society raise your children?

Pastor Hagee encourages fathers to be involved in their children’s lives, to know what they are listening to and the shows they are watching. Don’t follow Hollywood’s version of what the father should look like. We are to follow God’s plan, to be a living portrait of His will for our lives. The father is the prophet of the family in God’s economy. He is the guiding priest for the members of his household. In the Word of God he is the unquestioned leader.

The greatest battle in the home is the fight for authority; two leaders will only end in chaos. Pastor Hagee gives us scriptural guidance for how the father can lead a healthy household in the way of the Lord.
items.name: Portrait Of The Father

items.description:
Sermon 2 of the 4 part series, Family Matters

The portrait of a mother is found in Proverbs 31. Her children rise up and call her blessed. The Bible paints the portrait of a woman as a successful mother, first and foremost. Abraham Lincoln said, “The hand that rocks the cradle rules the world.” Pastor Hagee tells us that America’s future greatly relies on the mother and how she raises her children.

America today is supported by the god of the state, relying on welfare instead of looking to God to be their supply. Mothers are supposed to protect their children, not allow society to dictate how they are raised or leave their care to another individual. Jobs are never more important than children, and children should never be considered a job. They are an inheritance from the Lord. Giving birth does not make you a successful mother. Raising your children in the fear and admonition of the Lord is the greatest gift you can give them. Listen to these great illustrations of God’s portrait for a mother.
items.name: Portrait Of The Mother

items.description:
Sermon 3 of the 4 part series, Family Matters

Children today live in a jungle. Public schools have become a battle ground. Pastor Hagee says that God’s plan for the nation was what our country was built upon, but we have turned away from the portrait He originally painted, the ideal He intended for us. Child abuse is a tragic epidemic in our country, leaving children angry and frustrated. Children belong to parents to raise, not the state. Parents are to raise their children in the fear and admonition of the Lord so they know which path to follow and how to gain success in their own lives.
items.name: Portrait Of The Children

items.description:
Sermon 4 of the 4 part series, Family Matters

You will either raise your children by the law of the jungle or the Law of God. There is no other alternative. Pastor Hagee says that the family living inside of your house is either spirit-filled or controlled by the system based upon the choices made each and every day. We are vessels of the Holy Spirit, and God literally lives in us if we are children of the Most High God. As Christians, we choose to walk in the light while others fumble around in darkness. We have a higher calling.

A parent must choose to follow the path that God has chosen for their children, to guide and direct them towards a prosperous future through Jesus Christ. We are people of covenant and should behave differently than those living in the world. The Bible says that we are to train up a child in the way he should go so that when he is older he will not depart from the Word of God hidden in his heart. God is faithful to finish the good things He starts in the life of your children, but as a parent you must plant the seed and lead by example.
items.name: Portrait Of The Parents

items.description:
Sermon 2 of the 7 part series, 7 Secrets Of Success

Success is a journey that is a life-long adventure. We are used to having our way, right away. As a society, we don’t want to wait for anything. We want instant gratification. Pastor Hagee says there comes a time when quit looks good. Remember..it is always too soon to quit! Persistence is enjoying the distance between the promise of God and the provision of God. Persistence is going to the place of your failure and trying again. Persistence tells the mountain to move by faith. If God be for you, who can be against you? You can do all things through Christ! Never give up the fight! Let God arise and let His enemies be scattered!
items.name: The Persistence Principle

items.description:
Sermon 2 of the 8 part series, Joseph's Journey: From The Pit To The Palace

The favor of God is better than riches. It is the golden key to the gates of heaven. Every man or woman that God used throughout Scripture has these words written about them…”They found favor (grace) in the sight of God.”

Pastor Hagee says if there is one thing that can bring every dream to fruition it would be the favor of God. The favor of God causes demons to tremble and angels to come out on full alert ready to do battle on your behalf. Joseph had favor with both God and man, even though his circumstances might have been precarious. God never forgot about him and never forsook him.

You are also highly favored of God. You are royalty. No matter what you look like on the outside or the struggles you are going through, God is still on your side. You are blessed and can know the favor of God today just like Joseph did as he traveled from the pit to the palace.
items.name: The Favor Of God

items.description:
Sermon 3 of the 8 part series, Joseph's Journey: From The Pit To The Palace

Pastor Hagee tells us that our destiny is not staying in the pit. Our destiny is found in the palace where we can experience a full and abundant life. There is not one day of your life that is accidental. There is not one hour that the Divine Hand is not sculpting your future.Even when Joseph was sold as a slave, God was with him. If any part of his story was changed, we would probably have never heard of him. But because each piece was orchestrated by God, he is still able to touch the lives of people today.

As a child of God you are not controlled by anyone other than Almighty God. It may look like things are not going well right now, but God is dragging you toward the palace. It’s going to be great when you get there. God is on His throne and everything is going to be alright! Look up and get ready to receive your divine destiny! Let God help you fulfill your dreams!
items.name: Behold The Dreamer Cometh

items.description:
Sermon 4 of the 8 part series, Joseph's Journey: From The Pit To The Palace

Pastor Hagee says, “Your intolerance of your present condition creates your future.” Will you learn to live in misery instead of doing what you can to improve your situation? Don’t acclimate yourself to misery! Don’t become accustomed to sin, that which Satan is using to minimize your potential. God has not given us a spirit of fear. No matter what ails you, God is the Great Physician and He can heal you. We may not know what tomorrow holds, but we know Who holds tomorrow.

God has blessings just waiting for you. All you need to do is follow His plan for your life, ask Him to lead you and begin to drown in God’s favor. Don’t settle for the pit! Head for the palace! Satan attacked Joseph because he knew Joseph’s potential. He always attacks those who are next in line for a promotion. If Satan is attacking you, it’s because he knows your potential and he wants to kill your dreams. Stay the course, and know that God will restore unto you all that Satan has taken.
items.name: Joseph In The Pit

items.description:
Sermon 6 of the 8 part series, Joseph's Journey: From The Pit To The Palace

After 12 years of pain and reversal, Joseph is about to receive his great reward! Today is pay day! As it was with Joseph, so it is with us. Pastor Hagee says, “You may be facing a dark day in your marriage or a financial reversal, but the same God that protected Joseph can protect you.” When you least expect it, He will show up and begin to bless you with blessings you cannot contain. Your enemies will come one way and scatter seven ways.

Joseph maintained a positive outlook while he was in prison and was suddenly and unexpectedly promoted to the palace. Once he was released and brought before Pharaoh, Joseph did not point a finger of blame at those who wrongly imprisoned him. He was favored of God and promoted to a place of prominence…forgiving those who had lied about him and contributed to 12 long, painful years. God used him to lead an entire nation in their darkest hour. And today He is still using the story of Joseph to teach us how to have the best of things (God’s peace and favor) in the deepest valleys so that we can be promoted to a palace of our own.
items.name: Joseph In The Palace

This fabulous series will make a profound difference in your life and your family's lives.

Included with the purchase of the entire series is a copy of a Blessing you can pray over your loved ones

items.description:
Sermon 1 of the 5 part series, Ruth: The Romance Of Redemption

The book of Ruth is called the romance of redemption. It is a book that is written as a love story, and yet the word “love” is never mentioned one time in this book. In this teaching, Diana Hagee talks about the deep love that grows between a woman and her mother-in-law.

The love stories found in the book of Ruth are not the sexual attraction found in tabloids, but a deep spiritual connection that bonds two people for life. Listen to this lesson and learn the background on the history of the book of Ruth as Mrs. Hagee delves deep into the Greek and Hebrew meanings behind each chapter and verse. This is a story of redemption and grace that you don’t want to miss.
items.name: Ruth: The Romance Of Redemption

items.description:
Sermon 2 of the 5 part series, Ruth: The Romance Of Redemption

In this teaching, Diana Hagee encourages you to dive deep into the Word of God in order to arrive at your divine destination. Get excited about the Bible; be passionate about your relationship with Jesus Christ! Don’t worry about what those around you are thinking or the hurtful words they are spewing. Focus on what the Spirit is telling you. Cry out to God and share your needs with Him, your desires and your dreams. And know that He is able to meet you where you are to take you to a brand new dimension of praise and worship.

Listen as Mrs. Hagee walks through the book of Ruth and the Jewish Festivals to explain how this precious book is a reminder that every good and perfect thing comes from above.

Sermon 3 of the 5 part series, Ruth: The Romance Of Redemption

Sermon 5 of the 5 part series, Ruth: The Romance Of Redemption

Do you like to read love stories? Then this is the teaching for you! This grand finale to Diana Hagee’s series on Ruth, the Romance of Redemption details the great attraction between Ruth and Boaz that forms into a deep love one for the other.

Listen as Mrs. Hagee discusses the intricate details of how they met, and how their relationship grew into a love for the ages. You will truly enjoy hearing the deep traditions found in this great Jewish love story that actually took place so many years ago, starting in the middle of a field…proving that when God has a plan for you, He will meet you right where you are and show you amazing things that you never even saw coming!

items.description:
From Genesis to Revelation, the Bible places a premium on being a person of integrity who keeps their word. The inability of people to keep their commitments is a great weakness of our generation. 

There is no word in the Bible more meaningful than the word "covenant." The God of the Bible is a God of covenant. The Old Testament is a covenant. The New Testament is a covenant. 

God made covenant with Noah by placing a rainbow in the sky Promising that he would not destroy the world again by flood. That rainbow still appears today. God made a covenant with Abraham, Isaac and Jacob that the land of Israel would be theirs forever. That covenant still stands. 

God made a covenant with David that his seed, specifically Jesus Christ, would reign on His throne forever in the City of Jerusalem. God will keep his covenant and Jesus will come and reign over all the earth from Jerusalem. 

Every feature of the Bible is bound together by covenant. Throughout history, God has never done anything of importance without making a covenant. This series explores the life-changing covenants of God. It will truly revolutionize your life.

items.description:
Anger is a powerful emotion that can be used to build someone up or tear them down. It is justified if the cause is godly, but you must look at the motivation behind your anger. Jesus became enraged when he walked into the temple and saw that it had become a marketplace.

Pastor Hagee walks us through the synagogue that had become a bargainer’s paradise. Much like our world today, there was little room for prayer. We are reminded that when the cause is righteous, anger is love’s clearest voice. As Christians, we are called to be motivated by righteous indignation. Stop being seduced by the things of this world, and start standing up for what is good and pure. Put on the whole armor of God and fight the good fight.

items.description:
Fear is mentioned in the Bible more than 600 times, but Jesus commands us to “fear not” the things of this world. Pastor Hagee explains how we will either conquer fear or fear will conquer us. Like any emotion, fear can be a good thing. The fear of God is the beginning of wisdom. Learning how to bridle our fear is key.

In life we do many things because we fear painful consequences. But just like we are told to raise up a child in the way he should go, God disciplines us as well. God planted the emotion of fear in our moral nature to make us uneasy with our sin. If we fear an eternity spent in hell, we are sure to look to a Savior who can redeem us. It is not a matter of if you will bow, only a matter of when.

items.description:
If we are able to master our emotions, we can have unlimited success. We worry about many things: finances, health, marriage, our children. Pastor Hagee points out that, “Worry is like a rocking chair. It will give you something to do but won’t get you anywhere.” He defines worry as something over which we cannot have our own way.

In reality it is personal irritation with God. The Bible says to be anxious for nothing. God is greater than any problem you are facing. Demons tremble when you pray. Talk, act and think like a child of the King. Unleash the power of prayer in your life, and watch as your worry melts away. Rejoice! Good things are on the way!

items.description:
In this age of modern technology, we have learned to control everything but ourselves. Do you have discipline in your life? Pastor Hagee walks us through the path of destruction caused by living a life without discipline or self-control, pointing out that we are our own greatest enemy.

The Bible says that he who conquers a city is not as strong as the man who conquers himself. Discipline is the ability to make yourself do the things you have to do with excellence when they ought to be done. Life is not about doing what you want. The battle for self-control can determine if your life will be successful or end in utter disaster. Jesus calls us to be disciples. We must bridle our own emotions and follow Him in all that we do in order to reach rich fulfillment.

In this age of modern technology, we have learned to control everything but ourselves. Do you have discipline in your life? Pastor Hagee walks us through the path of destruction caused by living a life without discipline or self-control, pointing out that we are our own greatest enemy.

The Bible says that he who conquers a city is not as strong as the man who conquers himself. Discipline is the ability to make yourself do the things you have to do with excellence when they ought to be done. Life is not about doing what you want. The battle for self-control can determine if your life will be successful or end in utter disaster. Jesus calls us to be disciples. We must bridle our own emotions and follow Him in all that we do in order to reach rich fulfillment.

People are constantly searching for happiness.  They try to attain contentment more diligently than anything else.  We try to earn more and have more. We only end up wanting more and the hole that we are longing to fill gets bigger.  People need to stop looking to the world and its material possessions to satisfy them.  To find happiness, you only need to look to one source - the Word of God.
 
The Bible is what holds the secret to personal happiness.  It is God's desire to open the window of heaven and bless His children with blessings that we cannot contain.  Yet, it is our responsibility to place God first and be in the position to receive His blessings.  This series teaches you the biblical principals that are sure to make you among the happiest and most content Christians on earth.

Supplication means a petition, a request, a plea, a prayer. Prayer is the lifeblood to our existence as Christians. Prayer is a miracle; it is the ability to talk to God! The incredible thing about prayer is that God is waiting to hear us so that He can answer them and give us the desire of our hearts. Diana Hagee walks you through this beautiful teaching showing you that in prayer we praise Him, we thank Him and we trust Him. We are instructed in Philippians to “be anxious for nothing, but in everything, by prayer and supplication, with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God.” When making our supplications known to our Father with thanksgiving, praise and worship the indwelling of the Holy Spirit will guide us into all truth. A must for a deeper spiritual walk with Christ.

The resurrection is an event that our entire faith is built upon. Apostle Paul said in 1 Corinthians 15:14, “If Christ is not raised from the dead…our preaching is empty and our faith is in vain.”

In Christ’s resurrection, He signed, sealed and delivered our salvation for eternity. Jesus is alive and seated at the right hand of God our Father. He is the victor over death, hell and the grave. With the resurrection, every prophecy was fulfilled and every miracle was confirmed.

The same God who raised Jesus from the dead is still resurrecting the dead everyday. He is resurrecting dead marriages, broken lives shattered by sin, failed businesses and broken bodies. If there is an area in your life that needs resurrection, this series reveals the power of Christ and how His great glory can change your life forever.

items.description:
The Committed Life

What does the word, "commitment", mean? The dictionary defines commitment as "to pledge oneself to a position on an issue...to bind or obligate yourself as a promise or assurance...to send into battle for the defense of a righteous cause...to hold ourselves to the highest standards" and finally, "the action of entrusting one’s soul to God."

God honors commitment. What are you committed to? Are you committed to your career, your family, your children, your church? The Bible tells us in Micah 6:8 to be committed to the good.

This humorous and enlightening teaching by Diana Hagee will have you laughing out loud as she takes you through instances in her life that have required such commitment. A beautiful insight into the Hagee family as they have sought guidance from the Lord on how to live "The Committed Life."
items.name: The Committed Life

If you are at your breaking point emotionally, physically, spiritually, or financially and wondering if you can go on - know that “weeping may endure for the night but joy cometh in the morning!”

Pastor Matthew Hagee takes you through 4 steps to breaking through your breaking point.  In order to receive your breakthrough, you’re going to have to let go of what’s in your hand so that God can give you what He has in His hand for you!
product.name: The Breaking Point

items.description:
The Bible says “by our words are we justified or condemned.” 

Pastor Matthew Hagee teaches that from Genesis to Revelation, the Bible is concerned about every word that comes out of our mouths. 

The Bible says “out of the heart springs forth the issues of life.” We see in the Word of God that your mouth and your heart are connected to each other. The Bible tells us that the power of life and death are locked inside your tongue. Your tongue, like a small spark, can start an un-controllable wild fire in your life and in the lives of others. 

This series opens up the Word of God and instructs you so that you do not allow your tongue to control you, but teaches you how to begin to control your words so that you can accomplish God’s perfect will for you. Know that by the power of your words, you can receive the blessings of God.
items.name: The Purpose Of The Tongue

items.description:
What if this was your last year?  What would you really do different?  Would you make different decisions if you knew they would impact your eternal life?
 
In this exciting sermon, Pastor Matthew Hagee encourages you to examine your heart.  The reality is that Eternity is forever.  The decisions you make now impact your eternal life.  Do you share Christ with your neighbor?  Do you put something off hoping for more time?  Life is but a moment on earth, but eternity is forever.
items.name: The Reality Of Eternity

items.description:
The more you read through the pages of God’s Word, the more you begin to discover that we are privileged to be the children of the God who can do all things. The God who can speak into utter darkness and chaos and command light and order it to come shining through. The God that can breathe into a pile of dust and man becomes a living being. Nothing is too hard for God. Our God is stronger than the strongest and mightier than the mightiest. 

In this series, Pastor Matthew walks you through the supernatural things that God has done throughout the pages of scripture. Then he asks that you walk through what God has done in your own life. Recite all of the awesome things that Almighty God has done and begin to count them from the very simple to the absolutely complex.  Thank Him for your next breath and for the extraordinary gift of your redemption and everlasting life. In ALL things PRAISE HIM for NOTHING IS TOO HARD FOR GOD!
items.name: There Is Nothing Too Hard For God Pt. 1

items.description:
Build An Ark
What happens in the world around us is going to have an effect on us all. It seems that we are being faced with crisis is a daily occurance. Economically, the American dollar is weaker than it has been in decades. Spiritually, Christians are being attacked on all sides. Politically, our nation is more divided than it ever has been.
Between earthquakes, tsunamis, wars, protests and massive civil unrest, the world at large is in a very precarious state.
The Bible teaches us that wise people look at the environment that surrounds them and plan accordingly. The Word instructs that the wise pay attention at times like these and make a plan to be prepared. Pastor Matthew Hagee walks you through how to plan, or build an ark, for you, your family and those you love.

items.description:
To fully realize the enormity of the gift that is the Ten Commandments, you have to understand the context in which they were given.  God gave the Commandments to Moses after he freed the children of  Israel from the bondage of the Egyptians.
 
In Egypt, Pharaoh owned the Hebrews, they were his property.  Are you in Egypt right now?  Are you controlled by the sin that controls you?  In the Word, St. Paul says "you are either a servant to sin and Satan or a servant of Jesus Christ."  So, whose servant are you?
 
You need to understand the rich benefits of keeping God's Commandments and the dire consequences that wait for those who don't.
items.name: The Scarlett Letter A

items.description:
There are many topics in the Book of Daniel, but the most resounding of them all is the one that you will find from the first word in the chapter to the last line of the final page; and that is what a Mighty God we serve!

God is so mighty that even though Daniel finds himself in the midst of tough and sometimes horrific situations he can enjoy the best of things. God is so mighty that even though he is captive in a foreign land, God stands faithfully beside him. Even though Daniel is in a hostile environment, living in political unrest and uncertainty on every side…God Almighty still favored him. God’s hand was still upon him.

Pastor Matthew Hagee shows you that no matter what crisis you may be facing, the Mighty God of the Book of Daniel is the same yesterday, today and forever. He is mightier than your sorrow and He is faithfully beside you!
items.name: Living In The Lion's Den
